info.headline: High Wind Warning issued April 19 at 2:40PM MDT until April 19 at 6:00PM MDT by NWS Cheyenne
info.description: ...HIGH WIND WARNING NOW IN EFFECT UNTIL 6 PM MDT THIS EVENING... * WHAT...West winds 35 to 45 MPH with gusts up to 65 MPH. * WHERE...Central Laramie Range and southwest Platte County including the Bordeaux Interchange along Interstate 25. * WHEN...Until 6 PM MDT this evening. * IMPACTS...Mainly to transportation. Strong cross winds will be hazardous to light weight or high profile vehicles, including campers and tractor trailers.
info.instruction: A High Wind Warning means a hazardous high wind event is expected or occurring. Sustained wind speeds of at least 40 mph or gusts of 58 mph or more can lead to property damage.
